title: Google\Cloud\AssuredWorkloads\V1beta1\Workload
name: Workload
description:
An Workload object for managing highly regulated workloads of cloud customers.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.assuredworkloads.v1beta1.Workload

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Optional. The resource name of the workload. Format: organizations/{organization}/locations/{location}/workloads/{workload} Read-only.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Required. The user-assigned display name of the Workload. When present it must be between 4 to 30 characters. Allowed characters are: lowercase and uppercase letters, numbers, hyphen, and spaces. Example: My Workload

params.name: data.resources
params.description: Output only. The resources associated with this workload. These resources will be created when creating the workload. If any of the projects already exist, the workload creation will fail. Always read only.

params.name: data.compliance_regime
params.description: Required. Immutable. Compliance Regime associated with this workload.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. Immutable. The Workload creation timestamp.

params.name: data.billing_account
params.description: Input only. The billing account used for the resources which are direct children of workload. This billing account is initially associated with the resources created as part of Workload creation. After the initial creation of these resources, the customer can change the assigned billing account. The resource name has the form billingAccounts/{billing_account_id}. For example, billingAccounts/012345-567890-ABCDEF.

params.name: data.il4_settings
params.description: Required. Input only. Immutable. Settings specific to resources needed for IL4.

params.name: data.cjis_settings
params.description: Required. Input only. Immutable. Settings specific to resources needed for CJIS.

params.name: data.fedramp_high_settings
params.description: Required. Input only. Immutable. Settings specific to resources needed for FedRAMP High.

params.name: data.fedramp_moderate_settings
params.description: Required. Input only. Immutable. Settings specific to resources needed for FedRAMP Moderate.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Optional. ETag of the workload, it is calculated on the basis of the Workload contents. It will be used in Update & Delete operations.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Optional. Labels applied to the workload.

params.name: data.provisioned_resources_parent
params.description: Input only. The parent resource for the resources managed by this Assured Workload. May be either empty or a folder resource which is a child of the Workload parent. If not specified all resources are created under the parent organization. Format: folders/{folder_id}

params.name: data.kms_settings
params.description: Input only. Settings used to create a CMEK crypto key. When set a project with a KMS CMEK key is provisioned. This field is mandatory for a subset of Compliance Regimes.

params.name: data.resource_settings
params.description: Input only. Resource properties that are used to customize workload resources. These properties (such as custom project id) will be used to create workload resources if possible. This field is optional.

params.name: data.kaj_enrollment_state
params.description: Output only. Represents the KAJ enrollment state of the given workload.

params.name: data.enable_sovereign_controls
params.description: Optional. Indicates the sovereignty status of the given workload. Currently meant to be used by Europe/Canada customers.

params.name: data.saa_enrollment_response
params.description: Output only. Represents the SAA enrollment response of the given workload. SAA enrollment response is queried during GetWorkload call. In failure cases, user friendly error message is shown in SAA details page.
